threads.title: [SOLVED]820 3536 no data from SSD or USB
threads.message:
This came in with liquid and corrosion around <CAPACITOR>C7090</CAPACITOR>-<CAPACITOR>C7092</CAPACITOR> and F7005... Very quick easy power issue. Board powers and chimes but only shows flashing folder. I have tried booting to USB. It will power USB but not read it. With OPTION held down with USB and SSD I get only the network option, no available drives. Is this thing EFI locked you think? Doesnt show pad lock on screen...


Update - Not EFI locked and SSD works in another machine. 3.3V at L3700. CPU?...

[SOLVED]820 3536 no data from SSD or USB
threads.message: Both USB not working. They power on but nothing recognised.

threads.title: [SOLVED]820 3536 no data from SSD or USB
threads.message: Sounds like a clock issue, but then it would also not see any networks so confirm that. If it does not see networks check 24MHz on Y1915 and check traces.

threads.title: [SOLVED]820 3536 no data from SSD or USB
threads.message:
No networks... Checked around area you suggested and noticed that L1295 didnt look great so I changed it and things are now working. 
Thanks Duke... Appreciate it.
